New Records: Max Fried pitched seven innings of one-run ball, no earned runs, allowing five hits and a walk while striking out eight.
Key Match Events: Atlanta Braves' 3-1 win over the Toronto Blue Jays
Pre-Game Insights: The Braves are trying to lock down a playoff spot, and having another ace in full form can get them to October.
Post-Match Reflections: Travis d'Arnaud said Max Fried is very good at staying calm and just has to execute.
Max Fried said his goal is to give it all he has to get back to the postseason.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Braves are tied for the third and final Wild Card spot with the Mets.
The Braves have closed the gap on the Padres and Diamondbacks to 3.0 and 1.5 games back for spots one and two respectively.
Others: The Braves continue their playoff push on Saturday as they look to win their series against the Blue Jays.
